OL,3,CFamily of woman who went missing 12
OL,4,Cyears ago want death legally recognised
OL,6,FThe family of a 96-year-old woman who
OL,7,Fwent missing in Brighton 12 years ago,
OL,8,Fare pleading for the courts to
OL,9,Fpronounce her dead.
OL,11,FIt's thought Nellie Herriot was
OL,12,Fsuffering from dementia when she was
OL,13,Flast seen getting off a bus in the
OL,14,FWhitehawk district of the city on 23
OL,15,FApril 2012.
OL,17,FOne of Nellie's closest relatives, her
OL,18,Fgreat-nephew, George Holland, said he
OL,19,Fthinks the four year wait to declare
OL,20,Fher death is an insult to Nellie.
